Text:
@angelinadekirk

The subtitles are in three languages - Portuguese, English and Espanol (Yes, all in the same sub file). If you use VLC Media Player, just play the video, right-click -> Subtitles -> English. If you are running VobSub for subtitles - start the video,  right click the VobSub (green arrow) icon in the system tray and choose English. If you are using another software for subtitles, try and find out how to play a particular language from a sub file which has multiple language.

I had almost deleted the avi when opened it and found the non-english subtitles. Found this post while looking for english sub downloads. Then this possibility of multiple subs hit me. The info should have mentioned these three languages.
